# Worklog GitHub + DevOps Guardrails

This repository ships an MCP server. Favor stable automation and small reviewable changes.

## Branching strategy

- Never push directly to `main`.
- Create short-lived branches:
  - `feat/<topic>` for features
  - `fix/<topic>` for bug fixes
  - `chore/<topic>` for non-feature maintenance
  - `docs/<topic>` for docs-only updates
- Keep branch scope narrow; one logical change per branch.

## Commits

- Use Conventional Commits:
  - `feat:`
  - `fix:`
  - `chore:`
  - `docs:`
  - `test:`
  - `refactor:`
  - `ci:`
- Prefer small commits with clear intent.

## Pull requests

- Open a PR for every branch merged into `main`.
- PR title should follow Conventional Commit format when possible.
- PR description must include:
  - why this change exists
  - what changed
  - test evidence (`npm test` output summary)
  - risk/rollback notes when behavior changed
- Keep PRs small enough to review in under 20 minutes when practical.

## CI expectations

- Run `npm test` locally before pushing.
- Do not merge if CI fails.
- If CI fails, fix in the same branch before requesting review again.

## Release and tags

- Create a release only for meaningful shipped milestones.
- Tag from `main` after PR merge using semver:
  - `v0.x.y` while pre-1.0
  - `v1.x.y+` after stable API contract
- Version bump guidance:
  - patch (`x.y.Z`): bug fixes, no API break
  - minor (`x.Y.z`): new backward-compatible functionality
  - major (`X.y.z`): breaking behavior or contract changes
- Release notes should summarize user-visible behavior and migration steps.

## MCP-specific safety

- Keep runtime dependency count at zero unless explicitly approved.
- Validate all tool inputs strictly and preserve path-traversal protections.
- Do not introduce shell interpolation in core server logic.
- Maintain JSONL audit writes for write/verify/emission paths.

## Agent execution defaults

- If a task changes behavior, add/update tests in the same PR.
- If changing protocol/tool schemas, update docs in `README.md` or `docs/`.
- Avoid broad refactors mixed with feature delivery unless requested.
